rComments: idk... i mean she's a nice lady and all but honestly, she puts so much info in her slides and it confuses you so much. It's a real headache. I don't think I'll take another class with her again... also, i really dont like her grade distribution because it can really screw you over.

Definitely has a lot of knowledge about the material and always asks  Why or how? . Make an effort to attend her classes. She gives examples and explanations that might show up on an exam. The format was closely related to HSS3705, so students were focused on memorizing diseases, and their related jobs. Participate in class, it's worth it.

Excellente professeure. Elle s'assure que les étudiants comprennent avant de continuer et demande la participation des questions. Elle donne aussi la chance de poser des questions. Les examens sont très clairs et reflètent bien le contenu du cours. Il y a tout de même beaucoup de matière. Je l'ai adorée!
Très bonne professeur, elle est passionnée, patiente, elle veut que les élèves réussissent. Ses questions d'examens sont faciles et claires et tout est dans les powerpoint.

She came off a little cold in the beginning, but was nicer at the end. Know everything on the slides and you should be ok. Go to class too because her slides are incomplete and she doesn't post the complete ver online all the time. Can be very specific in midterms, so be ready for that. I thought I'd like this class but it was honestly meh.
Excellent teacher! She makes sure everyone understands before moving on. Her exams are quite easy as well!
